<br>
If any cleric nukes &quot;after&quot; eating a rod, it's insta /cast 8 (and my guild knows this after several incidents).<br>
<br>
If I see anything &quot;other&quot; than a cleric or wizzard eating rods, it's insta /cast 8.<br>
<br>
Why would I need the raid leader to tell me to leave?  I'll refuse the rods by going and xp'ing, no sence in sticking around to argue with them.  Eventually they learn, and raid leader has reeeeeeeeeemed necro's, druids, shaman, etc for eating rods.  Why should trod dispursement me my problem?  If raid leader needs/wants trods there, then it's his problem, he can deal with the perpetrators, while I xp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xalmat>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 221<br> <font color=#333333>(9/30/02 2:15:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm31.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: SURVEY II: Do you think it is appropriate for the...  </span><hr size=1> For once P1V1, we share the same opinion :P<br>
<br>
Only difference for me is that i need to /book 8 to mem Gate, before I /cast 5 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umadaamstier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mada Amstier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#333333>(9/30/02 2:42:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm31.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: SURVEY II: Do you think it is appropriate for the...</span><hr size=1> Bottom line, for any high end  content, you will have to CoH.  You will have to make mod rods.  If you don't want to do that, then don't join guilds for high end content.  Magicians are the mana factory.  Without mana, you won't be taking down those bosses in VT/SSRA where fights are anywhere from 15-40 mins.  Why is there all this clam about what classes can use rods?  All classes play a part.  If you fight mob x and you get adds, chanters will be using those rods to keep that mob mezzed while you still work on the high end boss.  If your shaman are using rods, you might want to wait for them to get Cann V abilities before you do any high end content.  Clerics, self explanatory why they need rods.  No heals, tanks die, good job on coffin cr.  If there are extra numbers of clerics, of course they are going to throw out nukes.  Again more DPS, faster the mob dies.  And again, if you already made your rods you will have time to nuke.  Wizards = DPS.  Feed them rods all day.  Druids = secondary healers, let them help heal mages/those on rampage/clerics absorbing damage from gflux etc.<br>
<br>
If you want to nuke, get a nice stack of rods out.  Watch how fast they go, if there is a steady supply, throw in nukes now and then.  CoH's are the same way, if the rods are low, tell those to chill until rods are up to speed, then summon those into camp.<br>
<br>
When I am in camp for a boss, I start stacking and rotating rods right away.  By the time he is engaged, there are usually at least 50+ rods ready for use.  That way you have time if you want to do something else such as nuke or need to coh stragglers.  <br>
<br>
Sometimes I am the only mage.  When there are others its just bonus to the raid.  Sending pets in for high end content, well for some mobs that may work but I usually don't send a pet in.  I like to win because thats more loot for us and we can move onto the next mob.  Sending pet puts you right on the aggro list and its just a matter of time when you get on some mobs rampage list and get eaten.  Of course damage shields will do that if your slacking on those...  Less aggro, more rods you can do.  A dead mage is useless and especially if you are the only one.  <br>
<br>
Only way I see this raid leader telling you to leave is simply your not doing your job as a mage.  Why be there if you don't want the raid to succeed.  You need to anticipate whats going on.  <br>
<br>
Closing - don't like what your being asked to do, then your playing the wrong class or your just simply playing it wrong.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Mada Amstier, ArchMage<br>
the Rathe<br>
